law.text:
The Division of Emergency Management may promulgate administrative regulations which address minimum training requirements and standards of response for individuals, agencies, and organizations who respond to the following search and rescue missions:
Searching for missing, lost, or overdue person or persons;
Cave rescue;
Dive rescue and recovery of drowning victims;
Inland water search, rescue, and recovery;
Search dogs and handlers; testing and certification;
Urban search and rescue; and
High angle or rough terrain rescue and recovery.
